author: ggregory
msg: I committed a refactoring to trunk which failed in Continuum because I used a String Java 6 API (getBytes(Charset)). Welcome to 2012, almost 2013 ;) I believe using this API is the best way forward and similar to other code in Commons.
This commit updates the POM and continuum for builds with Java 6 for the 3.3-SNAPSHOT.
If someone wants to keep running on Java 5 /and/ wants a bug fix post release 3.2, it will be in a 3.2.x release.
